external_knowledge:
- "Images" are media items of type 'Image';
- "Collection" is a grouping mechanism for media items;
- "More than one collection" indicates the image is part of at least two different collections.

- A media item can be a subject of another media item, forming a hierarchical structure;
- The hierarchy is built recursively, starting from the top-level items (those without a subject);
- Creators and subjects are associated with media items, and statistics are calculated for them;
- The cumulative count of creators who have created more than 10 media items is calculated for each subject;
- The results are ordered by the hierarchy level and media item title, with a limit of 100 results.

- "Unique artists" refers to distinct creators of media items;
- "Left their mark" means the creators have contributed media items;
- "Gallery" is a metaphor for the location where the media items are found.

sql:
SELECT mi.location_id, COUNT(mi.media_id) AS item_count
FROM media_items mi
GROUP BY mi.location_id;

external_knowledge:
